<br>
Ear: Gold Jasper Earring<br>
Ear: Gold Jasper Earring <br>
Neck: Chrysoberyl Talisman<br>
Face: Silver Ruby Veil (I know! I'm saving up for a Platinum ruby veil)<br>
Head: Nightshade Wreath<br>
Shoulders: Braided Ivory Cords<br>
Arms: Nathsar Arms<br>
Wrists: Runed Mithril Bracers<br>
Wrists: Chipped Bone bracer<br>
Hands: Splitpaw hide gloves<br>
Finger: Platinum Jasper Ring<br>
Finger: Platinum Diamond Wedding ring<br>
Chest: Foremans Tunic<br>
Back: Kunzar Cloak<br>
Waist: Crystalline Belt<br>
Legs: Imbued Vale Studded Leggings<br>
Feet: Acolyte's Anklet<br>
1HB: Dark Ember<br>
Secondary:Testament of Vanear<br>
Range: Small Wisdom Diety<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
So, keeping in mind my sadly small amount to spend, what can you reccomend? (I'll take hand-me-downs, lol, though I doubt I would!) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/3/02 8:59:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26360.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I wear?</span><hr size=1> I'd aim for Thurgadin quest bracers, grey flesh gloves and a shissar scale cloak, though each of them may run you a bit over what you already have in PP, so you'd have to do some earning first, or a lot of fighting in Kael and the Grey (many mobs red to you in both places). <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=126501">Abru</a>, Elder Hierophant on The Nameless,  <a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net/index.shtml" target=_top>Legacy of Steel</a>, <a href="mailto:AbruEQ@hotmail.com">AbruEQ@hotmail.com</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/3/02 10:17:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26360.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I wear?</span><hr size=1> Please don't be offended, but you should farm some hill giants for some quick pp (or do it with a partner or group), and before you know it, you'll have around 3kpp to spend, if not more. Once you have some more savings you can upgrade all your jewelry -- hell if you get the components, I'm sure you can find a jeweler to do the combines for a small fee -- and upgrade your gloves, cloak, boots. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugman20001969.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gman20001969</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 11:31:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26360.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I wear?</span><hr size=1> Heck I'm jealous. I made my main druid all wrong too and my wis is only at 130 right now. There are a few items that you have that I would kill for.<br>
<br>
I plan on getting my WIS up there with doing a few qwest with my guildies and such. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujhnkelly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jhnkelly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 7:18:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26360.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I wear?</span><hr size=1> look at the shroud of nature. drops in nurga i think. also look at getting eboots.<br>
<br>
i did the same thing as you. i created a druid halfling with low wisdom.  almost equal to you.  has been a pain to get it up. <br>
<br>
now i am 47 with 193.<br>
<br>
one other thing. look at doing shawl 3. doing that right now. gives you a 3 wis ranged item.<br>
<br>
kelahorn<br>
47 druid<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufrisleafshadow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>frisleafshadow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 8:20:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26360.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I wear?</span><hr size=1> HG's good exp at 40 too if I remember right (this was WAY pre-kunark as well) <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65433>fris</a>

<blockquote type=cite><blockquote><hr>"We need to make sure everything is working properly before we can patch this stuff -Alan "<hr></blockquote></blockquote></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/02 8:53:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26360.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I wear?</span><hr size=1> Once you get enough plat saved, you can maybe think about this path -- plan your budget:<br>
<br>
Ear: Gold Jasper Earring <b> > Forest Loops (a pair should be cheap)</b><br>
Ear: Gold Jasper Earring <br>
Neck: Chrysoberyl Talisman <br>
Face: (I know! I'm saving up for a Platinum ruby veil) > <b>Velium Ruby Veil (again, if you buy the components, just pay for the combine)</b><br>
Head: Nightshade Wreath > <b>Othmir Fur Cap maybe</b><br>
Shoulders: Braided Ivory Cords > Heh start working on shawl quest maybe<br>
Arms: Nathsar Arms<br>
Wrists: Runed Mithril Bracers<br>
Wrists: Chipped Bone bracer<b> > Nathsar Bracer</b><br>
Hands: Splitpaw hide gloves <b> > Grey Flesh maybe</b>  <br>
Finger: Platinum Jasper Ring <b>can be upgraded to Velium</b><br>
Finger: Platinum Diamond Wedding ring<br>
Chest: Foremans Tunic<br>
Back: Kunzar Cloak<br>
Waist: Crystalline Belt<br>
Legs: Imbued Vale Studded Leggings<br>
Feet: Acolyte's Anklet <b>Coldain Skin Boot or GEBs like 2kpp</b><br>
1HB: Dark Ember<br>
Secondary:Testament of Vanear <b>Get a shield later if you want more AC... Charred Guardian Shields are very affordable for you, so are Ry'Gorr Oracle Shields.</b><br>
Range: Small Wisdom Diety <b>Doing shawl part 3 yields Seal of Thoridain</b><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=morrene>Morrene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/5/02 8:30:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26360.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I wear?</span><hr size=1> Thank you so much for your help! Unfortuantly, the odds I'll get to camp the Shroud of nature are slim to none at the moment. But all the other suggestions are great! Thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bindy>Bindy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/5/02 6:05:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26360.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What should I wear?</span><hr size=1> HG's are good for pp loot, but you'd be better off being a port monkee for a night or 2... I've made 1kpp in a 3 or 4 hour taxi session before (just camp the taxi channel and shout your service in each zone you land in - the high end, slightly out of the way zones tend to earn you more as peeps will pay well to get out).  And yes, this was before I had my lvl 44 ports - tis still possible to make good money without having all destinations.  oh, and be sure to have /role off for the peeps that do a /who druid before doing a /shout to ask for a port...<br>
<br>
As for doing the shawls just to upgrade your shoulders - hmm, very time consuming...  you wont do better on wis than your ivy cords till you've got the 6th shawl... <br>
<br>
Good luck my friend! :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#333399>- </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove>The Druids Grove</a><font color=#333399> - </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment>Druidic Equipment</a> <font color=#333399> - </font><a href="http://www.thedruidsgrove.org">The Druids Grove</a><font color=#333399> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.4.7<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  